                        "Thomson (1897): Plum-pudding model — electrons embedded in positive charge",
                        "Rutherford (1911): Nuclear model — tiny dense positive nucleus with orbiting electrons",
                        "Bohr (1913): Quantised orbital model — electrons in discrete energy levels",
                        "Quantum mechanical model (1920s–present): Electron probability clouds (orbitals)"
