            "The Q-value determines whether a reaction is exothermic (Q > 0) or endothermic (Q < 0) — calculated from mass differences",
            "Cross sections (barns) quantify reaction probability and vary enormously with energy and projectile type",
            "The compound nucleus model explains most low-energy reactions as two-stage processes",
            "Direct reactions (stripping/pickup) probe single-particle nuclear structure at short timescales",
            "Thermal neutrons induce the largest cross sections — essential for reactor operation",
