            "Both fission and fusion release energy because products have higher binding energy per nucleon than reactants",
            "Fission of ²³⁵U releases ~200 MeV per event; D-T fusion releases 17.6 MeV but far more energy per unit mass",
            "A self-sustaining chain reaction occurs when k_eff = 1 (critical); controlled by rods, moderation, and inherent feedback",
            "Delayed neutrons (0.65% of fission neutrons) are essential for the controllability of fission reactors",
            "Reactor types differ by fuel enrichment, moderator, and coolant — all are designed around the same fission physics",
            "Fusion requires temperatures exceeding 100 million K — Coulomb barrier overcome by quantum tunnelling at Gamow peak",
            "The Lawson criterion (nτ_E ≥ 10²⁰ m⁻³·s) defines the minimum confinement conditions for net fusion energy",
            "ITER (magnetic confinement tokamak) aims for Q = 10; NIF (inertial confinement) achieved ignition (Q > 1 at target) in 2022",
            "Tritium for D-T fusion must be bred from lithium using the fusion neutrons themselves",
            "Nuclear fission is a major low-carbon electricity source today; fusion remains the most promising long-term energy prospect"
