                    definition: "A phasor is a rotating vector (in a complex plane) whose length represents the amplitude of a wave and whose angle represents its phase",
                    representation: "y = A e^(iφ) = A(cosφ + i sinφ); the physical displacement is the real part: y = A cosφ",
